                    <history>
                        <origin from="1450" to="1550">
                            <p>The manuscript was written in <origPlace>Denmark</origPlace>. The text was written over several decades. The
                                texts on the original parchment part were written in the <date notBefore="1450" notAfter="1499">second half of the fifteenth
                                    century</date>, while the younger texts in the paper part date
                                to the <date notBefore="1500" notAfter="1550">first half of the sixteenth
                                    century</date>, giving the manuscript an overall dating of
                                    <origDate notBefore="1450" notAfter="1550">c.
                            1450-1550</origDate></p></origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>
                                <name type="person" key="PedHan001">Peder Hanssen</name> owned the
                                manuscript in <date when="1569">1569</date> (f. <locus from="147v" to="147v">147v</locus>) and <name type="person" key="OluGre001">Oluf Gregersen</name> states himself as the owner of the
                                manuscript in <date when="1570">1570</date>. According to the note
                                on <locus from="147r" to="147r">147r</locus> he was born <q>y
                                    Lomburg Sogenn vtj hiegaarth</q>. <name type="person" key="PedSkr001">Peder Skriver</name> borrowed the book from
                                    <name type="person" key="OluGre001">Oluf</name> in <date when="1573">1573</date>  and <date when="1574">1574</date>
                                (according to the notes on f. 147r and the upper pastedown).</p>
                        </provenance>
                    </history>
